Health authorities in the Democratic Republic of Congo will introduce a Johnson & Johnson Ebola vaccine in November in the country’s eastern provinces, to counter the current outbreak, they said. <img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-1268630" src="https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/ebola-disease-warning-sweden-2098956.jpg?resize=300%2C178&#038;ssl=1" alt="Ebola Virus" width="300" height="178" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/ebola-disease-warning-sweden-2098956.jpg?resize=300%2C178&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/ebola-disease-warning-sweden-2098956.jpg?resize=58%2C34&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/ebola-disease-warning-sweden-2098956.jpg?resize=260%2C154&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/ebola-disease-warning-sweden-2098956.jpg?resize=200%2C119&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/ebola-disease-warning-sweden-2098956.jpg?resize=560%2C332&amp;ssl=1 560w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/ebola-disease-warning-sweden-2098956.jpg?w=590&amp;ssl=1 590w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> The J&J vaccine will complement another vaccine manufactured by Merck, which has been administered to more than 225,000 people. It requires two injections eight weeks apart, unlike the Merck vaccine, which requires a single shot. The first batch of 500,000 doses of the J&J vaccine should arrive in Congo next week, the authorities said in a statement. The inoculation process will start in Goma in early November and then be extended to other provinces, Reuters reported. Congolese health authorities had announced the deployment of the vaccine last month but had not specified when the campaign will take place. ⤖Germany commits additional $4m to WHO in fight against Ebola ⤖WHO says Tanzania not sharing information on Ebola Since it first started in August 2018, the Ebola outbreak has killed more than 2,100 people, second only to the 2013-16 outbreak in West Africa that killed more than 11,300. Vanguard News Nigeria. Authorities in the Democratic Republic of Congo are planning to use a second Ebola vaccine to help control an outbreak that has killed more than 2,100 people. In July, former Health Minister Oly Ilunga opposed its use saying it had not been proved effective. But DR Congo health officials say… September 22, 2019 In "Health" The Ministry of Health on Thursday warned Congo’s Ebola outbreak has entered “a new phase” after a case of the deadly virus was detected for the first time in the northwest city of Mbandaka, with a population of about one million people. May 17, 2018 In "Health" Some 100 people have died in the Ebola epidemic in DR Congo over the past three weeks, taking the overall death toll in the latest outbreak past 700, according to health ministry data. April 6, 2019 In "Health"